The top six of South Africa&#39;s ruling African National Congress (ANC) party have approved the removal of Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan, ANN7 television reported on Tuesday, citing sources. ANC Secretary-General Gwede Mantashe, one of the ANC&#39;s top six, told Reuters he could not comment on the report. ANN7 also reported that Brian Molefe, ex-head of state utility Eskom, and former finance minister Nhlanhla Nene, were not in the running to replace Gordhan.